<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>CSS Transitions Test: transition-timing-function - steps(2)</title>
<link href="http://www.intel.com" rel="author" title="Intel" />
<link href="mailto:shiyoux.tan@intel.com" rel="author" title="Shiyou Tan" />
<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transitions/#transition-timing-function" rel="help" title="2.3. The 'transition-timing-function' Property" />
<meta content="interact" name="flags" />
<meta content="Test checks that the first parameter of 'steps()' function specifies the number of intervals." name="assert" />
<style>
  div {
    background-color: blue;
    height: 100px;
    transition-duration: 1s;
    transition-property: width;
    transition-timing-function: steps(2);
    width: 100px;
  }
</style>
</head><body>
  <p>Click the blue square. Test passes if the width of blue square grows <strong>twice</strong>.</p>
  <div></div>
  <script>
    (function() {
      var div = document.querySelector("div");
      div.addEventListener("click", function(evt) {
        div.setAttribute("style", "width: 300px");
      }, false);
    })();
  </script>

</body></html>